subSubSection.paragraph:
Descriptive notes.
Head-body 91 mm (type specimen), tail 73-78 mm, hindfoot 17-18 mm; weight c.13-5 g. Condylo-incisive length is 22:3-22-6 mm. In color and general appearance, the Mindoro White-toothed Shrew resembles the Luzon White-toothed Shrew (C. 
grayi
), but it is noticeably larger. In contrast to the Sibuyan White-toothed Shrew (C. ninoyi), the Negros White-toothed Shrew (
C. negrina
), and the Panay Whitetoothed Shrew (
C. panayensis
), the Mindoro White-toothed Shrew hasa thick tail, with numerous bristle hairs along its entire length. Compared to the Mount Malindang White-toothed Shrew (
C. grandis
), tail is thinner with fewer long hairs on proximal half, hindfeet shorter and heavily pigmented. Cranium is less elongate, and interorbital region slightly narrower. Compared to the Negros White-toothed Shrew, braincase is more globose, interorbital region broader.
